KW  - Spot-forward exchange rate relationship
KW  - Model noise
AB  - This paper conducts a race between models in terms of their ability to explain observed violations of uncovered interest parity. This is done by comparing the empirical performance of the `simple efficiency' hypothesis and the models which assume the existence of risk premiums. My analysis uses noise ratios which complement specification tests by showing the relative degree to which each model reconciles with the data. The empirical results imply that the risk premiums introduced by the latent variable model could significantly explain the deviation of forward exhange rates from the expected future spot rates.
